& [AcceptedTargetFrame] is the external theorem neighborhood
  + [ckn_family] is local epsilon regularity for suitable weak solutions using scale-invariant velocity and pressure quantities
    = source: Caffarelli, Kohn, and Nirenberg, Partial regularity of suitable weak solutions of the Navier-Stokes equations, Communications in Pure and Applied Mathematics 35(6), 771-831, 1982, doi 10.1002/cpa.3160350604
    = url: https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/cpa.3160350604
  + [ess_family] is endpoint L-infinity-time L3-space regularity and backward uniqueness
    = source: Escauriaza, Seregin, and Sverak, L3,infinity-solutions of the Navier-Stokes equations and backward uniqueness, Russian Mathematical Surveys 58(2), 211-250, 2003
    = url: https://www.pdmi.ras.ru/~seregin/Recent%20Publications/engESS3.pdf
  + [pressure_criteria_family] is regularity criteria stated with pressure bounds
    = source: Tran and Yu, Regularity of Navier-Stokes flows with bounds for the pressure, Applicable Analysis 2016 preprint copy
    = url: https://research-repository.st-andrews.ac.uk/bitstream/handle/10023/12230/Tran_2016_Regularity_AML_AAM.pdf?isAllowed=y&sequence=1
  + [one_scale_epsilon_family] is epsilon regularity through weak-strong uniqueness
    = source: Albritton, Barker, and Prange, Epsilon regularity for the Navier-Stokes equations via weak-strong uniqueness
    = url: https://prange.perso.math.cnrs.fr/papers/epreg-viaWSU.pdf

& [HypothesisMatchTable] is the current comparison surface
  + [row_001_project_tail_object] is local tail budget from the external active-cylinder route
    = project_status: source_extractable as a tail_module
    = accepted_quantity_match: partial
    = reason: it is pressure-adjacent and local, but currently recorded as far-field/cutoff debris accounting rather than pressure oscillation or pressure L3/2 smallness
